sentences: Nana Azuki (AZUKI七, Azuki Nana) (born July 26, 1974) is a Japanese musical lyricist and keyboardist under Giza Studio label.
section: N/A

sentences: She is a former member of the Japanese pop band Garnet Crow, primarily as the lead songwriter and keyboardist.
section: N/A

sentences: Since she was 4, and until she was 19, she took flute and piano lessons.
section: == Biography ==

sentences: After graduating from college in 1999, she began showing off her talents in a number of auditions.
section: == Biography ==

sentences: Her earlier works were associated with Maki Ohguro, Deen, Field of View, WAG and Wands.
section: == Biography ==

sentences: After creating the band Garnet Crow in 1999 as a indie band and in 2000 as a major band, she has been continuing providing work to a number of Giza Studio artists as Takaoka Ai, Shiori Takei, Hayami Kishimoto and Sayuri Iwata.
section: == Biography ==

sentences: She has also worked has to Hitoshi Okamoto on his solo work as lyricist.
section: == Biography ==

sentences: After Garnet Crow disbanded, she composed one song for the Japanese singer Meg in 2014.
section: == Biography ==

sentences: As of 2018, her whereabouts are unknown.
